<h2 id="opening-a-link-in-a-new-page">Opening a link in a new Page</h2>

<p>A link is presented in markdown as <code class="highlighter-rouge">[User Friendly Text](http://domain.com/)</code>. This will open link in the same page/window/tab. To open a link in a new tab we need to add <code class="highlighter-rouge">{:target="_blank"}</code> right after the href syntax or alternatively use the html <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;a&gt;</code> tag.</p>

<h2 id="filters">Filters</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>capitalize</strong> - capitalize words in the input sentence</li>
  <li><strong>ceil</strong> - rounds a number up to the nearest integer, e.g. <code class="highlighter-rouge">5 #=&gt; 5</code></li>
  <li><strong>downcase</strong> - convert an input string to lowercase</li>
  <li><strong>first</strong> - get the first element of the passed in array</li>
  <li><strong>floor</strong> - rounds a number down to the nearest integer, e.g. <code class="highlighter-rouge">4 #=&gt; 4</code></li>
  <li><strong>last</strong> - get the last element of the passed in array</li>
  <li><strong>prepend</strong> - prepend a string e.g. <code class="highlighter-rouge">foobar #=&gt; 'foobar'</code></li>
  <li><strong>slice</strong> - slice a string. Takes an offset and length, e.g. <code class="highlighter-rouge">llo #=&gt; llo</code></li>
  <li><strong>split</strong> - split a string on a matching pattern e.g. <code class="highlighter-rouge">ab #=&gt; ['a','b']</code></li>
  <li><strong>strip_html</strong> - strip html from string</li>
  <li><strong>strip_newlines</strong> - strip all newlines (\n) from string</li>
  <li><strong>strip</strong> - strips all whitespace from both ends of the string</li>
  <li><strong>upcase</strong> - convert an input string to uppercase</li>
</ul>
